OL,6,FIn the conclusions from the Royal
OL,7,FCollege of Surgeons, it said the team
OL,8,Ffound staff who were interviewed in
OL,9,Ftheir probe "extremely engaged, open
OL,10,Fand helpful", adding: "Within the
OL,11,Fconstraints of current challenges they
OL,12,Fwere facing, it was clear that staff
OL,13,Fworked very hard to offer the best
OL,14,Fpossible service for their patients."
OL,16,FThe appointment of the chief of
OL,17,Fsurgery was also highlighted as a
OL,18,Fpositive step, with the new boss
OL,19,Fdescribed as attentive and responsive
OL,20,Fwhen staff escalated concerns.
